.TH "phy_connect_direct" 9 "phy_connect_direct" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
phy_connect_direct \- connect an ethernet device to a specific phy_device
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" phy_connect_direct
.BI "(struct net_device *dev "  ","
.BI "struct phy_device *phydev "  ","
.BI "void (*handler)(struct net_device *) "  ","
.BI "phy_interface_t interface "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "dev" 12
the network device to connect
.IP "phydev" 12
the pointer to the phy device
.IP "handler" 12
callback function for state change notifications
.IP "interface" 12
PHY device's interface
